g into play.\par \par 212.4k If an effect attempts to attach an Aura in play to an object or player, that object or player must be able to be enchanted by it. If the object or player can\rquote t be, the Aura doesn\rquote t move.\par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par 212.5. Instants\par \par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 212.5a A player }{\f0\insrsid3761202 who has priority }{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 may play an instant card from his or her hand. Playing an instant as a spell uses the stack. (See rule 409, \ldblquote Playing Spells and Activated Abilities.\rdblquote )\par \par 212.5b When an instant spell resolves, the actions stated in its rules text are followed. Then it\rquote s put into its owner\rquote s graveyard.\par \par 212.5c Instant subtypes are always a single word and are listed after a long dash: \ldblquote Instant \emdash  Arcane.\rdblquote  Each word after the dash is a separate subtype. The set of instant subtypes is the same as the set of sorcery subtypes; these subtypes are called }{\i\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 spell types.}{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  Instants may have multiple subtypes. (You can find the complete list of instant subtypes under \ldblquote Spell Types\rdblquote  in the glossary at the end of this document.)\par \par 212.5d Instants can\rquote t come into play. If an instant would come into play, it remains in its previous zone instead.\par \par 212.5e If text states that a player may do something \ldblquote any time he or she could play an instant,\rdblquote  it means only that the player must have priority. The player doesn\rquote t need to have an insta