e in-play zone, and also in the in-play zone before the permanent flips, a flip card has only the normal characteristics of the permanent. Once the flip permanent in the in-play zone is flipped, the normal name, text box, type line, power, and toughness of the flip permanent don\rquote t apply and the alternative versions of those characteristics apply instead.\par }\pard\plain \s23\ql \li1200\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1200\itap0 \i\f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Example: }{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Akki Lavarunner is a nonlegendary creature that flips into a legendary creature named Tok-Tok, Volcano Born. An effect that says \ldblquote search your library for a legendary card\rdblquote  can\rquote t find this flip card. An effect that says \ldblquote legendary creatures get +2/+2\rdblquote  doesn\rquote t affect Akki Lavarunner, but it does affect Tok-Tok.\par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par 508.3. If you control a flip permanent, you must ensure that it\rquote s clear at all times whether the permanent is flipped or not, both when it\rquote s untapped and when it\rquote s tapped. Common methods for distinguishing between flipped and unflipped permanents include using coins or dice to mark flipped objects.\par \par 508.4. Flipping a permanent is a one-way process. Once a permanent is flipped, it\rquote s impossible for it to become unflipped. However, if a flipped permanent leaves play, it retains no memory of its status. See rule 510, \ldblquote Status.\rdblquote \par \par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 509. Ending the Turn\