o within that player\rquote s range of influence. Range of influence covers spells, abilities, effects, damage dealing, attacking, making choices, and winning the game.\par \par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 601.2a The most commonly chosen limited ranges of influence are 1 seat and 2 seats. Different players may have different ranges of influence.\par }\pard\plain \s24\ql \li1500\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1500\itap0 \i\f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Example:}{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  A range of influence of 1 means that only you and the players seated directly next to you are within your range of influence.\par }{\b\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Example:}{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  A range of influence of 2 means that you and the two players to your left and the two players to your right are within your range of influence.\par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par 601.2b A player is always within his or her own range of influence.\par \par 601.2c The particular players within each player\rquote s range of influence are determined as each turn begins. \par }\pard\plain \s24\ql \li1500\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1500\itap0 \i\f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Example:}{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  In a game with a range of influence of 1, Alex is seated to the left of Rob, and Carissa is seated to the right of Rob. Carissa is not in Alex\rquote s range of influence. If Rob leaves the game, Carissa will enter Alex\rquote s range of influence at the start of the next turn.\par \par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 601.2d An object is within a player\rquote s range of influence if it\rquote s controlled by that player or by another player within that many seats of that player.\par \par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 601.3. Creatures can attack only opponents within their controller\rquote s range of influence. If no opponents are within a player\rquote s range of influence, creatures that player controls can\rquote t attack.\par \par 601.4. Objects and players outside a player\rquote s range of influence can\rquote t be the targets of spells or abilities that player controls.\par \par 601.5. Some cards require players to make choices. These cards work differently when the limited range of influence option is used.\par \par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 601.5a If a player is asked to choose an object or player, he or she must choose one within his or her range of influence.\par }\pard\plain \s24\ql \li1500\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1500\itap0 \i\f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Example:}{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  In a game with a range of influence of 1, Alex is seated to the left of Rob. Alex activates the ability of Cuombajj Witches, which reads, \ldblquote }{\f0\cf1\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Cuombajj Witches deals 1 damage to target creature or player and 1 damage to target creature or player of an opponent\rquote s choice,\rdblquote  targeting Rob and choosing Rob as the opponent who picks the other target. Rob }{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 must choose a target that\rquote s in both his range of influence and in the range of influence of the controller of Cuombajj Witches. He must therefore choose himself, Alex, or a creature controlled by either himself or Alex.\par \par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 601.5b If a player is asked to choose between one or more options (and not between one or more objects or players), he or she can choose between those options even if those options refer to objects or players outside the player\rquote s range of influence.\par }\pard\plain \s24\ql \li1500\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1500\itap0 \i\f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Example:}{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  Alex, who has a range of influence of 2, is seated to the left of Rob, and Carissa, who has range of influence of 1, is seated to the right of Rob. Alex plays a card that reads, \ldblquote An opponent chooses one \emdash  You draw 2 cards; or each creature you control gets +2/+2 until end of turn,\rdblquote  and chooses Carissa to make that choice. Carissa can choose the mode even though Alex is out of her range.\par \par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 601.5c If an effect requires a choice and there\rquote s no player who can make that choice within its controller\rquote s range of influence, the closest appropriate player to its controller\rquote s left makes that choice.