ns within Rob\rquote s range of influence. The ability of Rob\rquote s second Aura doesn\rquote t trigger, however, because that event includes the blocking creature, which is out of Rob\rquote s range.\par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 601.7a If a trigger event includes an object moving out of or into a player\rquote s range of influence, use the game state before or after the event as appropriate to determine whether the triggered ability will trigger. See rule 410.10.\par }\pard\plain \s24\ql \li1500\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1500\itap0 \i\f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Example:}{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  Carissa and Alex are outside each other\rquote s range of influence. Carissa controls a creature owned by Alex and they each control a Soul Net, an artifact which reads, \ldblquote }{\f0\cf1\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Whenever a creature is put into a graveyard from play, you may pay \{1\}. If you do, you gain 1 life.\rdblquote }{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  The creature is destroyed and is put into Alex\rquote s graveyard. Alex\rquote s Soul Net doesn\rquote t trigger because the destruction event was outside Alex\rquote s range of influence. Carissa\rquote s Soul Net does trigger, even though the creature is going to a graveyard outside her range, because the destruction event was within her range.\par }\pard\plain \s23\ql \li1200\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1200\itap0 \i\f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsi