re controlled by Alex, the player to Alex\rquote s left, and the player to Alex\rquote s right. No other creatures are dealt damage.\par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par 601.11. If a spell or ability requires information from the game, it gets only information from within its controller\rquote s range of influence. It doesn\rquote t see objects or events outside its controller\rquote s range of influence.\par }\pard\plain \s23\ql \li1200\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1200\itap0 \i\f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Example:}{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  In a six-player game where each player has range of influence 1, Alex controls Coat of Arms, which reads, \ldblquote }{\f0\cf1\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Each creature gets +1/+1 for each other creature in play that shares a creature type with it.\rdblquote  }{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Coat of Arms will boost Alex\rquote s creatures based only on what creatures are controlled by Alex, the player to Alex\rquote s left, and the player to Alex\rquote s right. It won\rquote t take other creatures into account.\par }{\b\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Example:}{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  In the same game, Rob is sitting to the right of Alex. Coat of Arms will boost Rob\rquote s creatures based only on what creatures are controlled by Rob and Alex. They are the only two players within range of both Rob and the controller of Coat of Arms.\par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par 601.12. The \ldblquote legend rule\rdblquote  (see rule 420.5e) applies to a permanent only if other legendary permanents with the same name are within its controller\rquote s range of influence.\par }\pard\plain \s23\ql \li1200\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1200\itap0 \i\f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Example: }{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 Alex has range of influence 1, and Carissa has range of influence 2. Rob sits between them. If Alex controls a legendary permanent and Carissa puts a legendary permanent with the same name into play, only the one controlled by Carissa will be put into a graveyard.\par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par 601.13. The \ldblquote world rule\rdblquote  (see rule 420.5i) applies to a permanent only if other world permanents are within its controller\rquote s range of influence.\par \par 601.14. Replacement and prevention effects watch for a particular event to happen and then completely or partially replace that event. The limited range of influence option can cause the modified event to contain instructions that can\rquote t be carried out, in which case the player simply ignores the impossible instructions. See rule 419, \ldblquote Replacement and Prevention Effects.\rdblquote \par \par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 601.14a If a replacement effect tries to cause a spell or ability to affect an object or player outside its controller\rquote s range of influence, that portion of the event does nothing.\par }\pard\plain \s24\ql \li1500\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1500\itap0 \i\f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\f0\insrsid37