igned in APNAP order. Other than that, the combat damage step proceeds just as in a two-player game. See rule 310, \ldblquote Combat Damage Step.\rdblquote \par \par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 603. Deploy Creatures Option\par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par 603.1. The Emperor variant always uses the deploy creatures option, and it can be used in other variants that allow players to compete in teams. Multiplayer formats in which players compete as individuals usually don\rquote t use this option.\par \par 603.2. Each creature has the ability \ldblquote \{T\}: Target teammate gains control of this creature. Play this ability only any time you could play a sorcery.\rdblquote \par \par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 604. Attack Left and Attack Right Options\par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par 604.1. Some multiplayer games use the optional }{\i\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 attack left}{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  or}{\i\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  attack right}{\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525  rules.\par \par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 604.1a If the attack left option is used, a player can attack only an opponent seated immediately to his or her left. If a player\rquote s nearest opponent to the left is more than one seat away, the player can\rquote t attack.\par \par 604.1b If the attack right option is used, a player can attack only an opponent seated immediately to his or her right. If a player\rquote s nearest opponent to the right is more than one seat away, the player can\rquote t attack.\par \par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 605. Free-for-All Variant\par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par 605.1. In Free-for-All multiplayer games, a group of players compete as individuals against each other.\par \par 605.2. Any multiplayer options used are determined before play begins. The Free-for-All variant uses the following default options.\par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par 605.2a The limited range of influence option usually isn\rquote t used in Free-for-All games. If it is, each player has the same range of influence, which is determined before play begins. See rule 601, \ldblquote Limited Range of Influence Option.\rdblquote \par \par 605.2b Exactly one of the attack left, attack right, and attack multiple players options must be used. See rule 604, \ldblquote Attack Left and Attack Right Options,\rdblquote  and rule 602, \ldblquote Attack Multiple Players Option.\rdblquote \par \par 605.2c The deploy creatures option isn\rquote t used in the Free-for-All variant.\par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par 605.3. The players are randomly seated around the table.\par \par 605.4. Free-for-All games use the normal rules for winning and losing the game. See rule 102, \ldblquote Winning and Losing.\rdblquote \par \par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 606. Two-Headed Giant Variant\par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par 606.1. Two-Headed Giant games are played with two teams of two players each.\par \par 606.2. No other multiplayer options are used in Two-Headed Giant games.\par \par 606.3. Each team sits together on one side of the table. Each team decides the order in which its players sit. The player seated on the right within each team is the primary player, and the player seated on the left is the secondary player.\par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 \par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\li600\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin600\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 606.4. The Two-Headed Giant variant has two unique features.\par \par }\pard\plain \s21\ql \fi-300\li900\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin900\itap0 \f4\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid3761202\charrsid10638525 606.4a Each team has a shared life total, which starts at 30 life.\par \par 606.4b. Each team takes turns rather than each player.\par \par }\pard\plain \s20\ql \fi-300\l